Subtitle
13
14 TO CREATE THE ARKANSAS 2036 COMMISSION.
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
17
18 SECTION 1. DO NOT CODIFY. TEMPORARY LANGUAGE. Arkansas 2036
19 Commission — Creation — Purpose — Members.
20 (a) There is created the Arkansas 2036 Commission.
21 (b) The purpose of the commission is to:
22 (1) Promote a suitable statewide observance of the two hundredth
23 birthday of Arkansas;
24 (2) Explore the possible construction of a commemorative landmark
25 that promotes tourism to the state;
26 (3) Cooperate and assist the Division of Arkansas Heritage with
27 programs commemorating the two hundredth birthday of the state; and
28 (4) Provide assistance for the development of programs,
29 projects, and activities promoting the history and heritage of the state.
30 (c) The commission shall consist of eight (8) members to include:
31 (1) The Director of the Division of Arkansas Heritage or his or
32 her designee;
33 (2) The Secretary of the Department of Education or his or her
34 designee;
35 (3) Two (2) members appointed by the Speaker of the House of
36 Representatives;
